âWell, whatâs the matter?â cried Claude, angrily, his crayon suspended
in mid-air; âwhat wasp has stung you now?â

He, whose knowledge of womankind was largely limited to professional
models, was at a loss to understand the girlâs action.

She neither spoke nor stirred, but remained with the counterpane tightly
