âI wonât eat you, will I?â urged Claude. âCome, just lie as you were,
thereâs a good girl.â

Again she blushed to her very ears. At last she stammered, âOh, no,
monsieur, no--pray!â

But he began to lose his temper altogether. One of the angry fits to
