âWell, you wonât, eh? But itâs idiotic. What do you take me for? Have
I annoyed you at all? You know I havenât. Besides, listen, it is very
unkind of you to refuse me this service, because, after all, I sheltered
you--I gave up my bed to you.â

She only continued to cry, with her head buried in the pillow.

âI assure you that I am very much in want of this sketch, else I
