embarrassed, and wishing too that she might have time to recover a bit.
Then he began again, in a very gentle tone:

âWell, as it annoys you, letâs say no more about it. But if you only
knew. Iâve got a figure in my picture yonder which doesnât make head-way
at all, and you were just in the very note. As for me, when itâs a
