She made a gesture of feigned surprise. âOh, dear me! you have
company--I did not know; Iâll drop in again.â

âYes, do,â said Mahoudeau, looking very vexed. âBesides, I am going out;
you can give me a sitting on Sunday.â

At this Claude, stupefied, fairly stared at the emaciated Mathilde, and
