plenty of room for their gestures; and they recovered breath there,
although they were always declaring that Paris was far too small for
them, and lacked sufficient air to inflate their ambitious lungs.

âAre you going anywhere particular?â asked Sandoz of Mahoudeau and Jory.

âNo,â answered the latter, âwe are going with you. Where are _you_
going?â

Claude, gazing carelessly about him, muttered: âI donât know. That way,
if you like.â

They turned on to the Quai dâOrsay, and went as far as the Pont de la
Concorde. In front of the Corps Legislatif the painter remarked, with an
air of disgust: âWhat a hideous pile!â

âJules Favre made a fine speech the other day. How he did rile Rouher,â
said Jory.

However, the others left him no time to proceed, the disputes began
