the gigantic bosom, and Lille, thrusting forward her huge bare foot.

ââIn the open airâ--it amuses them, eh?â he resumed. âAll right, since
they are bent on it, the âopen airâ then, the school of the âopen air!â
 Eh! it was a thing strictly between us, it didnât exist yesterday beyond
the circle of a few painters. But now they throw the word upon the
